The paper proposes a new learning approach for supervised and unsupervised Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision. The approach involves using mirror descent algorithm for exact maximum a posterior inference and back propagation with stochastic gradient descent for model parameter estimation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
